---
title: Hono
name: Hono
description: Send email from a Hono handler with the top-level mail().
category: Frameworks
---

Hono speaks the Web-standard `Request`/`Response`, so there's no framework magic: read the
request's `FormData` and hand it straight to [`mail()`](/api). Postboi extracts the
[special fields](/formdata#special-fields) and renders the rest into a tidy HTML table.

```typescript
// src/index.ts
import { Hono } from 'hono';
import { mail } from 'postboi';

const app = new Hono();

app.post('/contact', async (c) => {
	const form = await c.req.formData();

	// Reply-to comes from the submitted email, so replying reaches the sender.
	form.set('_reply_to', String(form.get('contactâ†’email') ?? ''));
	form.set('_subject', 'Contact Form');

	await mail({ body: form });
	return c.redirect('/?sent=1', 303);
});

export default app;
```

Point a `multipart/form-data` form at `/contact` with fields like `contactâ†’name`,
`contactâ†’email`, and `detailsâ†’message` â€” the [`fieldsetâ†’field`](/formdata#grouped-fields)
syntax groups them. The same handler works on any Web-standard runtime (Bun, Deno, Workers,
Node with an adapter).

The provider and default recipient come from [`postboi.config.ts`](/config) â€” a
`POSTBOI_TOKEN` routes to [Postboi Cloud](/cloud), or pick any [provider](/providers).

**Runnable example:** [`examples/hono-provider-postboi`](https://github.com/darbymanning/postboi/tree/main/examples/hono-provider-postboi).
